  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Espoir Pour les Communautes d&apos;Ouallam, Tillaberi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mercy Corps is implementing the Espoir pour les communaut&#xE9;s de Ouallam, Tillab&#xE9;ri (ECOUT) program over 24 months,ensuring support for households over two productive seasons. The program will reach the most vulnerable individuals in two communes. We work with local government, traditional leaders, other stakeholders and community beneficiaries to identify the most food-insecure households, as determined by the nutritional status of children, inability to access at least two diverse meals a days, and inability to purchase food. Mercy Corps ensures that pastoralist households, who are often left out of data collection activities and who face additional barriers to accessing assistance, are incorporated in all targeting exercises.</narrative>
  </description>
